{id global-tag-unit, h2 [Global Tag Unit]}
Global tag units are used to import css and unit compilers. A valid global tag unit should be at the beginning of a line of stdn.
[]
Multiple global tag units are supported. The value of css-src and ucs-src can be a urls file.
[]
Each global tag unit will be compiled to an empty div.
[]
{css-src hello.css, ucs-src hello.js, global []}
{two [
    {display [Source]}
    {display [Result]}
    {div [
        {lang stdn, code [
            '{css-src hello.css, ucs-src hello.js, global []}'
            '{name world, hello []}'
        ]}
        {dl [
            {dt [hello.css]}
            {dd [{src hello.css, lang css, block, code []}]}
            {dt [hello.js]}
            {dd [{src hello.js, lang js, block, code []}]}
        ]}
    ]}
    {name world, hello []}
]}
[]
[{href https://github.com/st-org/st-std/blob/main/src/ucs.ts, a [ucs.ts]}' is a good example to learn how to write unit compilers.']
